Docs.example:
Bad example:

if (type.GetInterface ("IConvertible") != null)  {
	// then the type can be assigned to IConvertible
	// but what if there is another IConvertible in there ?!?
}

Good example:

if (typeof (IConvertible).IsAssignableFrom (type))  {
	// then the type can be assigned to IConvertible
	// without a doubt!
}

